Description:
Real Family Living In Coburg's Best
Please register your interest to participate in a Brad Teal auction. Registrations allow us to maintain compliance with the latest government directions. All auctions will be held onsite and online. Please register to bid here: https://portal.bidtracker.com.au/auctions/449a520e-00bb-43a7-8294-03889d108a15/register-bidder/
Emphasising a wholesome family lifestyle, this superior four bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow offers more magic than meets the eye. Beautiful leadlight windows with decorative ceilings give original character as the contemporary extension showcases convenient versatility. Multiple living spaces present a sunbathed formal lounge that progresses into a modern kitchen fully equipped with stainless steel appliances, black tapware, tiled splashback and breakfast bar. The spacious meals/living is blanketed by an impressive vaulted ceiling with a wood fireplace, while opening to an all season alfresco and large landscaped garden. An extravagant master bedroom strategically hides a classy ensuite within the WIR, while the tiled central bathroom allows access from the additional accommodation, two with BIRs. Featuring floorboards throughout, family sized laundry, loads of storage, garden shed, long driveway providing sufficient OSP and heating/cooling. Within a family friendly pocket, it's surrounded by valued schools, O'Heas Bakery, Coburg North Shopping Village, parks, public transport, CityLink and vibrant Sydney Road.

Description:
Convenient Easy Living
*** Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations. ***
***Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.***
Just steps to Coburg North primary, and within a short walk from Coburg North Village, cafes, Harmony Park and transport, this well-maintained two bedroom plus study single level property would make an ideal first home, downsizer or investment. On its own low maintenance block, the freestanding brick home features open plan living/meals area incorporating modernised kitchen with quality bench tops and cabinetry. A rear study opens to a sizeable backyard. Private accommodation comprises two double bedrooms with built-in-robes and modern bathroom. Includes gas stove, ducted heating, split-system air conditioner, polished floorboards, off street parking at the front.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Elegant Style with Flexibility
Space, style, and quality ensures this majestic home is sure to impresses. The attention to detail throughout is nothing short of astounding and a prestigious array of extras all resulting in heart pounding exhilaration.
Boasting high ceilings throughout, downstairs includes a guest master bedroom with walk in wardrobe and your own semi ensuite. A light filled open plan dining/living area with European Oak timber flooring and adjoining onto the stunning kitchen. Featuring 900mm Bosch appliances including dishwasher, double sink under mount sink with Pendent lighting, double pantry, soft closing drawers, 40mm Calcutta stone bench tops with a waterfall finish and complemented by the tiled splash back. Leading out through the large sliding doors and onto your own private Merbau decking area, overlooking the landscaped rear yard and double lock up garage with internal staircase leading to your own private studio/office or fifth bedroom with kitchenette and bathroom.
Heading upstairs via the Victorian Ash hardwood staircase you will find three generous size bedrooms with two of them having built in wardrobes and are serviced by an immaculate shared ensuite with floor to ceiling tiles. While the master bedroom includes its own walk in robe and private ensuite with both bath tub and shower.
Additionally, this stunning family home includes is a separate fully functional laundry, Bosch alarm, Tech intercom system, blue stone tiled front porch, matte black fixtures throughout. Within walking distance to public transport, local schools, Upfield Bike path, the vibrant Sydney, Moreland and Melville Road with its cafes and restaurants on offer, ensuring that nothing is ever out of reach!

Description:
Elevated Sanctuary At Coburgs Peak
Find perfect harmony between the lush green landscape and this modern boutique complex in the highly demanded & rising pocket of Coburg. With pristine outlooks combined with contemporary designer style, this elevated & light filled sanctuary has been designed for simple yet lavish entertaining. Offering two bedrooms, tranquil views, expansive open plan living, and a prime location, this compelling apartment is a refined luxury.
Key points for this spacious lodging:
- Abundant natural light and accompanying verdant landscape views showcased by tall & bright ample windows throughout
- Master bedroom suite featuring gorgeous views, his & hers walk-in-robes, and a generous fully-tiled ensuite with fine line detail and rainfall shower
- Spacious 2nd bedroom featuring mirrored built-in-robes and balcony access
- Fully-tiled central bathroom with bathtub radiating with designer flair
- Embrace the light-filled open plan living/dining/kitchen area
- Mirrored kitchen splashback ignites culinary inspiration in the kitchen, served by Miele and Fisher & Paykel appliances, and stone tabletops
- Large multi-access balcony promising stunning views & a breath of fresh air
- European laundry that maximises space in the living zones
- Split-system air conditioning
- 1 Carpark on title
Embrace the natural excitement that Pentridge Village has to offer, with lake views and expansive reserves at your doorstep. Being just a moments walk to Coburgs popular shopping destinations, this location will not cease to amaze. Northland is only a short 10 minute drive away, providing the accessibility that home owners thrive for. Coburg High School, Batman Train Station, and tram stops are a short walk away, guaranteeing comfortable living for years to come.

Description:
From Cute to Cutting Edge...
****Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.****
Set to impress with its fabulous fusion of classic and contemporary, this captivating Californian presents an exceptional inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with its versatile design, first-class renovations and terrific living/entertaining spaces both inside and out. Flawlessly presented and filled with natural light, the home's stunning interior showcases three genuinely large bedrooms (all with built-in robes), modern two-way central bathroom and equally-impressive second bathroom with discreet laundry facilities. Add to this a vast and versatile open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a beautifully-appointed kitchen with stone benchtops/breakfast bar, tiled splashbacks, soft-close cabinetry and quality European appliances. High square-set ceilings throughout, the home also includes solid hardwood floors, gas heating and split-system air conditioning, plus a substantial backyard with extensive brick paving and wide undercover pergola, versatile studio and oversized double garage/workshop via side driveway. Walking distance to local buses, Melville Road trams, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, it's also close to Coburg Station and vibrant shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway.

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Position! Retro Glamour! Say hello to a comfortable Coburg lifestyle
* Register to attend an open for inspection*
In order to maintain a maximum of 20 attendees to all Open Inspections, we ask that you please register to attend. By registering your details, you avoid disappointment if more than 20 people attend the inspection and will assist us in keeping the inspections as safe as possible for our team and our clients.
Edwardian architecture meets retro vintage flourishes in this fabulously positioned three-bedroom Coburg home (land size 503sqm), set on two titles with R.O.W. access at rear, offering potential dual occupancy (STCA).
Infused with a delightful touch of old-world glamour thanks to its leadlight-framed front door, beautifully high ceilings and expansive windows, this lovely residence is far from ordinary.
Gliding to the end of a glorious hallway past each of the three exceptionally sizeable bedrooms, youll discover a cosy kitchen and dining space with ample cabinetry, spacious lounge, bathroom and a study or fourth bedroom.
The back door beyond the kitchen will lead you outside to a lush garden shaded by a large fruit tree (and hiding a concealed outdoor toilet!), providing a both a convenient and serene spot for outdoor entertaining.
Alongside it is a garage-cum-studio complete with laundry, cooking facilities, heater and cellar.
Enjoying easy access to Sydney Road, Coburg Farmers Market, the historic Pentridge Village, public transport, schools and parklands, this home offers an immediately comfortable lifestyle and malleable canvas that promises an abundance of options to renovate in the future, making it a wonderful home for every phase of family life.

Description:
Low-Maintenance Perfection with Every Coburg Advantage
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST: Closing Monday 22nd June at 5.00pm
***this property is available for inspection by appointment-Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
Surrounded by established gardens on its own separately-titled block, this freestanding townhouse delivers a lifestyle of easy-living excellence with its impressive design elements and long list of features - all in a sought-after south-of-Bell Street location. Beyond the attractive brick facade, discover a light-filled interior showcasing two large bedrooms (both with spacious built-in robes), together with a stylish central bathroom (with tub) and additional powder room. Adding to its appeal is a versatile open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a well-appointed kitchen complete with breakfast bar, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Ready to simply move in and enjoy, the home also comes with ducted heating and split-system air conditioning for all-seasons comfort, alarm, solid hardwood floors, full-size laundry and excellent storage options. Completing the picture is a wonderfully private north-facing courtyard with lush lawn area and perimeter gardens, plus the added advantage of a remote-control garage with internal entry. Moments from the open spaces of Coburg Bush Reserve, it's also walking distance to Coburg Station and choice of Sydney Road or Melville Road trams and numerous bus services, Sydney Road's renowned cafes and restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets, as well as easy access to the area's popular schools.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Period Prize Reimagined for Perfect Modern Living
***this property is available for inspection by appointment-Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
Ideally positioned in a family-focused Coburg neighbourhood, this gorgeous home retains all the allure of its Art Deco origins whilst providing an impeccable urban environment of uncompromised quality and class. Beyond the landscaped front garden and captivating facade, discover an expanded interior showcasing three generous bedrooms (all with fully-fitted robes), together with a luxurious master ensuite and equally-opulent main bathroom with freestanding tub and heated towel rails. Bathed in natural light, the home's spacious open-plan living and dining areas are complemented by a superb kitchen complete with Ilve dishwasher, Sirius undermount Rangehood, Steel Combi-Steam upright cooker with 4 gas burner (x1 Wok) and teppanyaki grill plate, Shaws double-bowl butler's sink and ample cupboard space. High ceilings throughout, other stand-out features include ducted heating and add-on refrigerated cooling, alarm system, solid hardwood floors (hallway with feature parquetry), stone benchtops and soft-close cabinetry, as well as motorised Velux roof windows (living area), concealed laundry facilities and excellent storage options. Bi-folds reveal a fabulous al-fresco entertaining area with built-in BBQ and integrated heater, plus a delightful back garden and double car garage with remote-control access via the side driveway and rear ROW. A short stroll to local buses and Melville Road trams, St Fidelis and Coburg West primary schools, it's also close to Moreland Station, Coburg's vibrant shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. Description:
Designed to impress
PRIVATE INSPECTIONS ONLY - PLEASE CONTACT US TO ARRANGE
In one of Coburg's best pockets lies this spacious newly built townhouse with a floor plan designed to impress. This home provides a fresh, functional and naturally lit open plan layout lending itself entirely to a comfortable and modern lifestyle.
Walking through the doors you are greeted by the formal living area with carpet underfoot. Leading through to a generous open plan dining/living and kitchen. The Kitchen features 40mm Caesar stone benchtops, soft closing 2pac cabinetry, double sink, 900mm stainless steel appliances and a walk-in pantry with plenty of storage space. Beyond the beautiful sheer curtains is the five panel bi-fold doors which takes your out to your own private courtyard with access to the double garage which can also be used as an undercover entertainment area for the family BBQ. Downstairs also includes a powder room.
Making your way upstairs you are greeted with a third living area and will also find three generously sized bedrooms. The enormous master bedroom features a walk-in wardrobe and an ensuite with floor to ceiling tiles, matte black fixtures and a stand-alone bathtub. The other two bedrooms include mirrored sliding built in wardrobes and serviced by a modern central bathroom.
Complementing this brand-new home is reverse cycle ducted heating and cooling, remote alarm system, LED downlights throughout and ROW access.
Perfectly positioned, within walking distance to public transport, local schools, Upfield Bike path, the vibrant Sydney, Moreland and Melville Road with its cafes and restaurants on offer, ensuring that nothing is ever out of reach!
